cff-version: 1.2.0
message: "If you use ChronoGauntlet, please cite it using these metadata."
title: "ChronoGauntlet: a datetime/timezone silent-wrong benchmark for LLM-generated code"
abstract: >-
  ChronoGauntlet measures whether LLM-generated code silently mishandles dates,
  times, and timezones: code that passes weak happy-path unit tests yet returns
  wrong instants at DST transitions, across naive/aware boundaries, on leap days,
  and in epoch/offset conversions. Candidates are judged by a fully executable
  oracle — a pinned-tzdata differential reference swept at adversarial instants —
  and scored by a per-model, per-pitfall silent-wrong-rate. No human labels, no
  LLM judge.
type: software
authors:
